# Environment variables

This monorepo uses two environment files:

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| [`backend/.env.example`](backend/.env.example) | Backend API, Discord bot, database, secrets |
| [`frontend/.env.example`](frontend/.env.example) | Frontend API base URL (optional for local dev) |

Copy each example to `.env` in the same folder and fill in your values.

**Do not commit real `.env` files.** Channel IDs and mirror webhook URLs are configured per admin in the dashboard Settings page after login — they are not stored in `.env`.
